Because of the excellent stability, the analytical applications of CDs were investigated. As shown in Fig. 3a, the fluorescence of CNDs was significantly quenched with the gradually increasing concentration of dopamine. The relationship can be expressed as F0
                           /F−1=0.2328+0.0979c with correlation coefficient of 0.9943 in the linear range from 20μM to 80μM (inset of Fig. 3a). Here, F0 and F are the fluorescent intensities of CNDs in the absence and presence of dopamine. The detection limit was calculated to be 0.0078μM based on 3σ/s (σ is the standard deviation of eight blank measurements; s is the slope of the calibration curve). This detection limit is comparable and even better than those reported in the literature (Table 1
                           ). Fig. 3b shows the high selectivity of CNDs towards dopamine in the comparison with some possible foreign substance. All these analyses reveal that the prepared CNDs can be served as an effective fluorescent probe for selective and sensitive detection of dopamine.

According to the knowledge that dopamine has high affinity towards Al3+ at the ratio of 2:1 at optimum pH7.4 [45]. Then we investigated the possibility of this designed CNDs-dopamine system for sensing Al3+ (Fig. 5a). Upon the addition of Al3+, the stronger interaction between Al3+ and hydroquinone groups of dopamine released the CNDs and recovered the fluorescence (Fig. 4). It is clear that the relative fluorescence intensity of this sensing platform exhibits a linear response to the Al3+ concentration ranging from 4μM to 40μM (Fig. 5b). The calibration curve can be expressed as F0
                           /F−1=−0.0058–0.0069c with correlation coefficient of 0.9928. F0 and F are the fluorescent intensities of CNDs-dopamine in the absence and presence of Al3+. The detection limit for Al3+ was calculated to be 0.0329μM based on 3σ/s (σ is the standard deviation of eight blank measurements; s is absolute value of the slope of calibration curve). This result limit is comparable and even better than those in the reported literature (Table 2
                           ). As shown in the inset of Fig. 5b, the fluorescence of the system recovered to 75% of the initial fluorescence of CNDs. While, upon the 120μM concentration of Al3+, the fluorescence of the sensing platform almost doesn't change any more.
